Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 25 KYODO -- The United Nations has 
formally requested Japan to send 15 election observers to El 
Salvador to join a UN team to monitor the March parliamentary 
elections, the Foreign Ministry said Friday [25 February]. 
  Japan received a written request on the matter from UN 
Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali, the ministry said. 
  The government will study the situation in various fields in 
El Salvador before deciding to send the election monitors, it 
said. 
  Salvadoran President Alfredo Felix Cristiani, during his 
visit to Japan in November, asked Japan to send election 
monitors for the March poll. 

